726980f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - Springfield Boulevard
726980f-b.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at the N. E. corner of Springfield Boulevard,
showing the Queens Village Church, Reformed in America. It was
formerly known as the First Reformed Church of 2ueens, the corner-
stone of which was laid by Dr. Creed,September 28, 1858. The chapel
is at the S. E. corner of the two above mentioned thoroughfares.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(2)
The same, at a later date.
March 4, 1927
P. L. Sperr

726981f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - Springfield Boulevard
726981f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at, and adjoining the S. E. corner of Spring-
field Boulevard, viewing eastward and showing the chapel and the
parsonage of the Oueens Village Church, Reformed in America. The
church proper is at the N. E. corner of the two thoroughfares. The
parsonage was the Combs House in 1873.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(2)
The parsonage and part of the chapel.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
(3)
Another view of the chapel, some years later.
March 4, 1927
P. L. Sperr
